  "body": "# Description\r\n\r\nWhen a user tries to restore his profile from a seed phrase, the default fleet will be used by the app. \r\nBut the backup could have been stored on a different fleet, because:\r\n- the default fleet might change with the app upgrade\r\n- the user is able to use custom peers/storenodes (not sure of this)\r\n\r\nIf we have an ability to select the fleet from UI settings, then I believe there should be ability to select a fleet to try to fetch the backup from. \r\n\r\n----- \r\n\r\nThe onboarding path I'm talking about: \r\n`Add existing Status user` -> `I don't have other device` -> `Enter a seed phrase`.\r\n",
